  "prompt": "Are all caterpillars butterflies?",
  "response": "No, not all caterpillars turn into butterflies. Caterpillars are the larval stage of two types of insects: butterflies and moths. So, while some caterpillars will eventually transform into butterflies, others will become moths. Both butterflies and moths go through a complete metamorphosis, changing from egg to larva (caterpillar) to pupa (chrysalis or cocoon) to adult (butterfly or moth).",
